@teddypompom how long are you there for and where are you staying? To be honest Dubai is all shopping sun and food.... Be sure to have some real good quality Lebanese food! Al hadeerah lebanese restaurant is amazing on a Thursday night. Expensive so if you book be sure to not eat all day so you can make the most of the all you can eat food! I love the cocktail roof bar at the one and only royal mirage on an evening! Be sure to have spa treatments somewhere any of the top hotels are good but the one and only royal mirage used to be great! All tourists do the sand dune experience it's fun but if you're not there for long it's not amazing... I'd choose sitting by the pool before that! Atlantis waterpark is amazing!!! As is the ice cream parlour in atlantis... Oh and the steak house in atlantis is SO good but again super pricey. Have an awesome time x

She has an apartment out there!? Lucky you!! Yeah I've been to the top, it's kind of one of those touristy things that's exciting while you're going up... But I'm terrified of heights so I crawled around the floor for the most part! I'd love to go up at night and watch the fountains from up there. Do it, you may as well! And then have lebanese food at the place close by, or go for drinks on the terrace at the address hotel bar opposite, fancy! X
